Our home SJHS Scholar Bowl Event will be held on Monday, February 13th, at SGS.
We will be hosting 200+ students, sponsors, and workers on this evening.
We will be serving snack mix and water.

We need your help in providing the ingredients for the evening!
We thank you in advance!

10 cases of water (20-24 package)

4 boxes of Chex cereal, any variety
4 boxes of Cheerios cereal, any variety
8 bags of milk chocolate chips
8 bags of baking M&Ms
8 bags of pretzels
8 boxes of cheese crackers
8 boxes of animal crackers
8 boxes of teddy bear crackers
8 bags of marshmallows

Please let us know what you can provide. Please leave the items at SGS by the end of the day on Friday, February 10th.

It's a great day to be a Tiger!

post_text:
It's a very busy time in Tiger Country! Thank you to our generous boosters!

*The sub-state volleyball hospitality room was very much appreciated! Thank you!
*We sent Jill Stephens off to the state Cross Country meet with a good bag! She placed 21st!
*This Tuesday we will support our SHS Tiger Football team, as an on-air supporter, for the game to be aired on the radio.
*We have also given a donation to assist SHS in feeding the Wallace County high school football team, coaches, and cheerleaders before they make the long trip home after the game on Tuesday night.
*Next Monday, November 7th, we will be feeding the students participating in the Scholars Bowl event here and the volunteers. We will be looking for donations for that event over the next few days!

Again, thank you so much! It's a great day to be a Tiger!

ATTENTION TIGER FANS!!! TIGER FANS ARE ENCOURAGED TO ATTEND THE STATE BASKETBALL GAMES ON FRIDAY AND SATURDAY AT EMPORIA. TRANSPORTATION WILL BE PROVIDED FREE OF CHARGE ON THE TIGER COACH BUS. BUS WILL LEAVE FRIDAY, 3/8/13 MORNING AT 10:30 AM FROM IN FRONT OF THE HIGH SCHOOL. SATURDAY'S DEPARTURE TIME WILL BE DETERMINED AFTER THE OUTCOME OF FRIDAY'S GAME. SEATS ARE FIRST COME FIRST SERVE. SATURDAY'S GAMES IF WE ARE PLAYING IN THE 3RD PLACE GAME BUS WILL LEAVE AT 8:00 AM AND IF WE ARE PLAYING IN THE CHAMPIONSHIP GAME BUS WILL LEAVE AT 11:30 AM. YOU WILL NEED MONEY FOR MEALS AND ADMISSION. COME OUT AND SUPPORT OUR TIGERS!!!

Fort Hays State Athletic Department would like to give your school and fans the opportunity to purchase advanced KSHSAA 3-2-1A State Wrestling Tickets for both Thursday, February 23 and Friday, February 24. To purchase tickets please go to:
